oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cliffview
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Cliffview, the home of Enoch Dougue, located on the Cumberland River. A fence and gate surround the home. The windows have shutters. Several rocking chairs are on the front porch. The entrance of the home has columns. Transom windows flank the front door. The second floor has a balcony.

North Carolinian Enoch Dougue (later known as Enoch Dozier) started building the home in 1812 near the Cumberland river. The property stayed in the hands of many generations of the Dozier family. Daniel Boone once stayed at the home.
